Then triangles $OBC$ and $OQC$ are 30-60-90 triangles, so $OQ = \frac{1}{2}.$

Also, $\angle ODP = 60^\circ,$ so triangle $ODP$ is a 30-60-90 triangle.  Therefore, $DP = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{3}$ and $OP = 1 - \frac{\sqrt{3}}{3}.$

Note that $AP = OP = 1 - \frac{\sqrt{3}}{3}.$  Also, $CP = 1,$ so by the Pythagorean theorem on right triangle $APC,$
\[AC = \sqrt{1 - \left( 1 - \frac{\sqrt{3}}{3} \right)^2} = \frac{2 \sqrt{3}}{3}.\]Then by Ptolemy's theorem on cyclic quadrilateral $PQBC,$
\[\left( \frac{1}{2} + r \right) \cdot AC = 1 + r,\]so
\[r = \frac{2 - \sqrt{3}}{9}.\]Hence, $a + b + c + d = 2 + 3 + 3 + 9 = \boxed{17}.$```

